# all parts needed

The PCB is from: https://jlcpcb.com 
You need to upload the Gerber Zip. 

I used the 5V ProMicro from: https://www.sparkfun.com/products/12640

SMD headers https://www.sparkfun.com/products/11542

Neopixels: https://www.sparkfun.com/products/16346

The frame is: https://www.maxkeyboard.com/max-keycap-cherry-mx-switch-gateron-switch-o-ring-ultimate-sampler-tester-kit.html

At least 16 0.1UF caps https://www.digikey.com/product-detail/en/kemet/C1206C104K5RAC7800/399-C1206C104K5RAC7800CT-ND/411524

Resistors:
8 10k ohm https://www.digikey.com/product-detail/en/yageo/RC1206JR-0710KL/311-10KERCT-ND/7321561
1 300 ohm https://www.digikey.com/product-detail/en/stackpole-electronics-inc/RMCF1206JT300R/RMCF1206JT300RCT-ND/1942776

Use any MX style switches. 

Max keyboard frame from: https://www.maxkeyboard.com/max-keycap-cherry-mx-switch-gateron-switch-o-ring-ultimate-sampler-tester-kit.html
